When I used to live in Adams Morgan 14 years ago, this was my go-to neighborhood joint for healthy, homestyle meals.  One of the things I used to do on Friday evenings was get a takeout order.  My favorites were the fall-off-the-bone lamb shanks stew; or the grilled chicken; or chicken kabobs - which all came with 2 sides and pita bread. They serve grilled salmon as well. They made, what I call rice-a-roni - better than that commercial brand - laced with subtle spices. Those family-sized​ portions always lasted me through the weekend.  I also remember every time I stopped by, I’d see folks ordering this stuff that looked like green and red peppers in olive oil 🤔. Finally, I tried it and it was soooo much better than I expected. It was actually eggplant in this luscious, mild tomato sauce with subtle seasonings that made it simply delectable! From that point on I always included this ‘stuff’ in my order by pointing to the ‘stuff’ through the glass display at the counter.  So, fast forward: I’m visiting my hometown and wondering if my neighborhood joint is still open…Hurray! I’m very happy to be in a familiar place seeing that not everything in DC has changed.  Guess what? I now know what that ‘stuff’ is - 😆! I ordered 4 along with lamb shank stew and the ‘rice-a-roni’ to take back to my home in NYC!  Homestyle, family-sized portions and a relaxed, no-nonsense​ atmosphere.  A family-run​ business. They must be doing something right.

Astor is a Mediterranean style take out restaurant with counter service deli options. If you call ahead it will probably take around 15 minutes or so to get your meal so I would definitely not consider this place fast food. Some of the entrees and meals are a little pricey for the feel of the place but overall pretty tasty. I have tried the chicken kabobs, kufta kabobs, and beef and lamb combo meals and enjoyed them all. If you want something cheap and tasty I totally recommend the Astor burger (basic beef burger patty seasoned with Mediterranean spices and feta cheese). It’s just under $5 out the door!

After living in the neighborhood for 8 years I've visited Astor too many times to count.  While it offers some very delicious items there are a few things to note:  - some of their food is pretty pricey for carryout - the wait is FOREVER, even if you call ahead - the food is inconsistent - when it's great it's great, but when it's bad it's terrible (i.e. hamburger meat, chicken brined too long sometimes, dry meat)  That being said I do continue to visit Astor, but only order certain items when I know that I will have 20+ minutes to wait for my order.

Great place, good service, great food!  This place has a wide variety of food, from mediterranean to sandwiches and pizza.  I love their half chickens and legs of lamb, and their side dishes are great; the "astor vegetarian" plate is like a sampler of the cold side dishes, and sometimes I get then even though I'm not vegetarian.  They also have great pitas.  I can't really vouch for their sandwiches and pizzas, though, because I usually stick with ethnic foods when I'm at an ethnic restaurant.  They don't do table service, generally.  You order at the counter and then they call your number when it's done.  You are supposed to bus your own table.  However, they are very friendly to us, and sometimes will bring it out.  Plus, this setup keeps the cost down (the place is pretty inexpensive) and you don't have to do a 15-20% tip, so I'm all for it.
